<DOC><DOCNO> AP900104-0086 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-01-04-90 1120EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r w PM-PeaceCorps-Poland     01-04 0134</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Peace Corps-Poland,130</SECOND><HEAD>Peace Corps Recruiting English teachers for Poland</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Peace Corps announced today it isrecruiting 60 teachers of English to train other teachers in Polandbeginning in June and that 90 more instructors will be needed nextyear.   ``We need very quickly to train 10,000 English teachers,'' saidPaul Coverdell, director of the Peace Corps. He said the requestfor trained teachers of English as a foreign language originatedwith Poland's new regime and that a formal agreement is expected tobe signed in February.   The Peace Corps recently began recruiting English teachers toserve in Hungary, training other teachers. The job requirements area degree in teaching English as a foreign language, a year'sexperience, U.S. citizenship and a willingness to serve abroad fortwo years.</TEXT></DOC>